      "content": "I understand that it feels like you're constantly running on empty, and the idea of finding a new purpose or coping mechanisms can seem overwhelming. It's okay to feel exhausted and to question the constant struggle. Sometimes, the most logical choice might be to focus on self-care and finding moments of peace, even if they don't feel like progress. It's important to remember that you're not alone in this, and it's okay to take things one step at a time. You don't have to keep fighting if you don't want to. Sometimes, it's okay to just be.",
